    back: 'A Certificate of Destruction (CoD) is a formal document issued by a destruction vendor confirming that specific devices were destroyed by a specific method on a specific date.\n\nContents: organization name, device make/model/serial numbers, date of destruction, method used, vendor name and certification, signature of the person who performed or witnessed destruction.\n\nWhy it matters:\n• Required evidence for compliance audits — HIPAA, PCI DSS, GDPR, SOX all require documented proof of proper disposal\n• Demonstrates due diligence if a data breach investigation occurs\n• Provides chain-of-custody documentation from pickup to completion\n\nFor the exam: a Certificate of Destruction is required documentation, not optional paperwork.',
