    back: 'Default usernames and passwords (admin/admin, admin/password, admin/1234) are publicly documented for every router model and are immediately exploited by automated internet scanners within minutes of a router going online.\n\nAn attacker with router admin access can:\n• Redirect DNS queries to malicious servers (DNS hijacking)\n• Open port forwarding to internal devices\n• Disable the firewall\n• Intercept all network traffic\n\nThe admin password should be strong and unique — different from the Wi-Fi passphrase. Remote administration from the WAN (internet) side should also be disabled; admin access should only be available from the internal network.',
