    topicId: 'topic-c2-2-10',
    front: 'What is a guest network and why should IoT devices be placed on it?',
    back: 'A guest network is a separate SSID running on its own VLAN, isolated from the main internal network. Devices on the guest network can reach the internet but cannot communicate with devices on the main network (file servers, printers, NAS, workstations).\n\nWhy IoT devices belong on the guest network:\n• IoT devices (smart TVs, thermostats, cameras, smart bulbs) often run unpatched firmware with hardcoded credentials\n• Many IoT devices are frequent botnet targets (Mirai botnet used IoT devices)\n• Isolating IoT limits the blast radius — a compromised smart thermostat cannot reach business files or internal servers\n• IoT devices rarely need to communicate with other internal computers\n\nBandwidth throttling can also be applied to the guest SSID to prevent guests from saturating the connection.',
