    back: 'Static port forwarding: a permanent rule that always forwards an external port to a specific internal IP:port combination. The port remains open 24/7 regardless of whether any internal device is actively using it. Lower security — the port is a continuous attack surface.\n\nPort triggering: a dynamic rule that opens an external port temporarily only when outbound trigger traffic is detected from an internal device. The port closes after a timeout when not in use.\n\nKey differences:\n• Port triggering: more secure (port only open when in use); supports multiple devices triggering the same port sequentially\n• Static forwarding: required for servers that must accept connections at any time; limited to one internal IP\n\nUse port triggering for gaming and applications that need temporary inbound access; use static forwarding for permanent services like web servers.',
