    back: '1. Disconnect from the network immediately — before anything else. Ransomware spreads to network shares, mapped drives, and other connected systems. Pulling the network cable or disabling Wi-Fi prevents further spread even if the encryption continues locally.\n\n2. Do NOT pay the ransom — there is no guarantee the attacker provides a working decryption key, and payment encourages further attacks.\n\n3. Restore from a clean backup — this is the correct resolution on the exam. The backup must pre-date the infection.\n\n4. Verify the backup is clean: cloud-synced backups may have synced the encrypted files, overwriting the clean versions. Offline or air-gapped backups are the proper defense.\n\n5. Report to management and potentially law enforcement (FBI Internet Crime Complaint Center — IC3).\n\n6. Determine the infection vector before restoring — fix the entry point so it does not happen again.',
