    back: '1. Identify and quarantine: run Windows Defender full scan + Malwarebytes. If ransomware: disconnect from network FIRST before scanning.\n\n2. Safe Mode if needed: restart into Safe Mode (hold Shift + Restart or F8). Loads minimal drivers — may prevent malware from loading and blocking removal tools.\n\n3. Remove detected threats: use the security tool\'s quarantine and removal. For stubborn malware, use a bootable rescue disk (runs outside the infected OS).\n\n4. Check persistence mechanisms: Task Manager Startup tab, Task Scheduler, shell:startup folders, browser extensions, installed programs list. Remove anything suspicious.\n\n5. Repair system files: DISM /Online /Cleanup-Image /RestoreHealth, then sfc /scannow. Malware often corrupts system files.\n\n6. Change all credentials: passwords for all accounts used on the infected machine — the machine may have had a keylogger. Notify IT security if work accounts were used.\n\n7. Verify and monitor: reboot normally; run scan again; monitor for 24–48 hours; check Event Viewer.',
