    back: 'Clean first when:\n• Infection detected early by AV before significant damage\n• Malware type is known with reliable removal tools\n• No evidence of rootkit activity\n• System is a workstation (not a server) with non-critical data\n• Time to clean is reasonable compared to reinstall + reconfiguration time\n\nWipe and reinstall (nuke and pave) when:\n• Rootkit is suspected or confirmed — rootkits modify the OS kernel and bootloader; complete removal is unreliable without reinstalling\n• Malware persists after multiple removal attempts\n• System files are severely corrupted beyond what DISM/sfc can repair\n• Corporate policy requires reinstall for confirmed infections (common in regulated industries)\n• Scope and dwell time of infection are unknown — damage may be beyond what is visible\n\nExam rule: if a question mentions rootkit or malware that keeps returning after removal → the answer is OS reinstall.',
