    id: 'fc-c2-3-4-08',
    topicId: 'topic-c2-3-4',
    front: 'A PC shows high CPU usage from an unknown process at idle. Walk through the diagnostic steps.',
    back: 'Scenario: unknown process consuming high CPU while the user is not actively doing anything.\n\n1. Open Task Manager (Ctrl+Shift+Esc) → Details tab. Right-click the process → Open file location to see where the executable lives. Legitimate Windows processes are in C:\\Windows\\System32. Processes in temp folders, AppData, or user profile folders are suspicious.\n\n2. Right-click the process → Search online to research the process name.\n\n3. Check Resource Monitor (resmon) → CPU tab and Network tab. Look for unexpected outbound connections — a process connecting to unusual IPs may be a botnet client, RAT, or cryptominer.\n\n4. Run Windows Defender full scan and Malwarebytes scan.\n\n5. Check startup entries (Task Manager → Startup) and Task Scheduler for scheduled tasks associated with the suspicious process.\n\n6. If malware is confirmed: follow the full malware removal procedure. If a rootkit is suspected based on symptoms (security tools won\'t run, process hides itself), proceed to OS reinstall.',
    difficulty: 3,
